## 3. Update your Delivery user with an SSH public key

You need to associate your public SSH key with your Delivery user. This key enables you to authenticate requests to Delivery from the command line.

If someone else set up the account for you, ask that person for your username and initial password. If you do not have a Delivery user set up, [do so now](/delivery/get-started/create-the-organization-and-add-a-user#step4).

Start by generating an SSH key. Run this from your PowerShell prompt. You can replace you@example.com with your email address. Press Enter when prompted.

```ps
