## 4. Install the Delivery CLI

You're now set up to access Delivery from the web interface. The web interface is where you manage your profile and review and approve changes made by others. Now you need to set up the Delivery command-line interface (CLI). The CLI enables you to submit new changes and pull down changes made by others.

Follow these steps to install the CLI. In the next step, you'll connect the CLI to your Delivery user account.

1. [Download the Delivery CLI installer for Windows](https://s3.amazonaws.com/delivery-packages/cli/delivery-cli-latest.msi).
1. Click the package and install.

The installer adds the path to the `delivery` executable to your system PATH. Either open a new PowerShell window and `cd` to your <% fp '~\delivery-demo' %> directory or run this command to update the PATH in your current session.

```ps
# ~\delivery-demo
$ $env:Path = $env:Path + ";C:\chef\delivery-cli\bin"
```

Finally, verify that you can access the CLI.

```ps
