## 7. Set your Git identity

Finally, run `git config` to set your [Git identity](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup#Your-Identity). Git includes this information as metadata when you commit changes.

If you have an existing Git account, such as with GitHub, you can use the same information here.

Here's an example.

```ps
# ~\delivery-demo
$ git config --global user.name "John Smith"
$ git config --global user.email jsmith@example.com
```

Your workstation is now set up.

